- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper deals with graph classes and their complexity.
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the question of logic capturing polynomial time is a fundamental problem in database theory.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper deals with the complexity of graph classes and their definability in logic.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with graph classes and their properties.
